Title: Punicalagin, a pomegranate compound, induces apoptosis and autophagy in acute leukemia
Authors: Paweena Subkorn, Chosita Norkaew, Kamolchanok Deesrisak, Dalina Tanyong
Study Population: NB4 (acute promyelocytic leukemia) and MOLT-4 (acute lymphocytic leukemia) cell lines
Vaccine Types: Not applicable – compound studied was Punicalagin, not a vaccine
Study Period: Not explicitly mentioned – experimental durations include 24 h and 48 h treatments
Outcome Measured: Apoptosis and autophagy induction in leukemic cell lines
